title: Netanyahu Scores Another Victory, but at What Price?
description: The Israeli prime minister has pushed through the first part of his judicial overhaul, but in doing so has deepened a rift in Israeli society and propelled the country into an uncertain new era.

title: Israeli Lawmakers Adopts Law Weakening Supreme Court
description: Complaining of an unaccountable judiciary, the far-right governing coalition, despite months of mass protests, voted to strip the court’s power to override “unreasonable” government actions.

title: Russia Strikes Danube Port, Escalating Attacks on Ukraine Grain Routes
description: The assault, across the river from Romania, heightened the risk of a more direct confrontation with a NATO member and came on the same day that drones struck buildings in Moscow.

title: Putin Signs a Harsh New Law Targeting Transgender People in Russia
description: The law, part of a broader L.G.B.T.Q. crackdown, includes a ban on transition surgery.

title: Protests in Israel Intensify After Vote on Judicial Limits
description: Outraged opponents of the government’s removal of some of the Supreme Court’s powers blocked roads around the country. Police responded on horseback and with water cannons.

title: Your Tuesday Briefing: Mass Protests in Israel
description: Also, political uncertainty in Spain and Twitter’s rebranding.

title: Macron’s Lesson After Riots? France Needs Order ‘at Every Level’
description: President Emmanuel Macron of France had outlined 100 days to move past protests over his pension reform, but rioting set off by a fatal police shooting jolted the country once more.

title: Israel’s Judicial Plan and Protests: What to Know
description: Israeli lawmakers advanced parts of a contentious plan by the right-wing government to reduce the power of the Supreme Court, defying threats by protesters to shut down large parts of the economy.

title: North Korea Launches Two Ballistic Missiles: What to Know
description: The test came two days before North Korea was set to celebrate the 70th anniversary of the 1953 armistice that ended the Korean War.

title: What the Collapse of Spain’s Far Right Means Going Forward
description: About the only thing clear from Spain’s muddled election results was that Spaniards were turning away from the political extremes.

title: Greta Thunberg Fined After Blocking Port Traffic
description: The climate activist said that trials like hers brought attention to climate change and that she would continue to protest.

title: Fires Strike Corfu and Evia in Greece as Rhodes Continues to Burn
description: New blazes broke out on Corfu and Evia as tourists were being flown home.

title: Russia-Ukraine War: Russia Strikes Danube River Port, Escalating Attacks on Ukrainian Agriculture
description: A drone attack on a port near Romania signaled that Moscow, after pulling out of a deal enabling Ukraine to ship grain via the Black Sea, is targeting its alternate export routes.

title: U.S. Confronts Tight but Turbulent Relationship With Israel
description: President Biden has cautioned Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu against pursuing a proposal to rein in Israel’s judiciary, a plan that has deeply divided Israeli society.

title: Russia Destroys Drones Targeting Moscow, and Blames Ukraine
description: Two buildings were hit but there were no reports of casualties. Video verified by The New York Times shows smoke and damage to several buildings.

title: China Gym Roof Collapse Claims at Least 11 Lives
description: A building contractor improperly stored material on the gym’s roof, official media reported. Most of the victims were children.

title: Iranian Mothers Choose Exile for Sake of Their Daughters
description: Some have risked their lives to escape to Iraq or other nearby countries, where they have found havens to start over.

title: Seeking Full Honors, Some Ukrainian Families Wait to Bury Their Dead
description: Thousands of families have buried soldiers in cemeteries across Ukraine in “Alleys of Heroes.” But some have held off, awaiting a version of Arlington National Cemetery.

title: End of Nigerian Fuel Subsidy Fuels Crippling Inflation
description: In his first two months in office, President Bola Tinubu has ripped the Band-Aid off Nigeria’s ailing economy. Time will tell if it can heal, but for now, Nigerians are feeling the pain.

title: Indonesia Boat Accident Leaves at Least 15 Dead
description: Nineteen other people were still missing on Monday, rescuers on the island of Sulawesi said.

title: Russia Says It Destroyed 2 Drones Targeting Moscow
description: Two buildings were hit and there were no reports of casualties. Video verified by The New York Times shows smoke and damage to several buildings.

title: Your Monday Briefing
description: An important vote on Israel’s political future.
